{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/make/robot/motors","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"planetary-gear-train\" style=\"position:relative;\">Planetary gear train<a href=\"#planetary-gear-train\" aria-label=\"planetary gear train permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Main question here is power and torque which is created by series of spur gears called a <em>gear train</em>. It could be simple as 2 gears or <strong>planetary gear train</strong> (higher gear reduction, very compact)</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/fb7863df4696067bd6f004b558878810/planetary_gear_train.gif\" alt=\"Planetary gear train\"></p>\n<p>and this can be implemented in non-circular form</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/d9bc9e1866380f099258b07571b51ee2/non_circular_planetary_gear_train.gif\" alt=\"Non-circular planetary gear train\" title=\"Credit: YouTube channel Rail and Oak\"></p>\n<p>\"Credit: YouTube channel Rail and Oak\"</p>\n<p>They are not as compact as round ones, and at specific points they hold higher stalled resistance than in others which makes movement obviously uneven.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"flex:1.5523809523809524;\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b9b7e38c6aa357045259b9930f365774/8e1fc/non-circular-gears.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 64.41717791411043%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Non-circular gears\"\n        title=\"Credit: Gertrude Stein and Alice B. Toklas Non-circular gears\"\n        src=\"/static/b9b7e38c6aa357045259b9930f365774/6aca1/non-circular-gears.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b9b7e38c6aa357045259b9930f365774/d2f63/non-circular-gears.jpg 163w,\n/static/b9b7e38c6aa357045259b9930f365774/c989d/non-circular-gears.jpg 325w,\n/static/b9b7e38c6aa357045259b9930f365774/6aca1/non-circular-gears.jpg 650w,\n/static/b9b7e38c6aa357045259b9930f365774/8e1fc/non-circular-gears.jpg 900w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Credit: Gertrude Stein and Alice B. Toklas Non-circular gears</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2 id=\"epicyclic-gearing\" style=\"position:relative;\">Epicyclic gearing<a href=\"#epicyclic-gearing\" aria-label=\"epicyclic gearing permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Planetary gearing (or <strong>epicyclic gearing</strong>) is cool, but there is also <strong>cycloidal drive</strong>, that eliminates a <em>backlash</em> - it's that imperfection between gear teeth that is noticeable when rotation direction has been changed.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/331e421aa6df4615285e8a6226820f24/cycloidal_gearing.gif\" alt=\"Epicyclic gearing\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"strain-wave-gearing\" style=\"position:relative;\">Strain wave gearing<a href=\"#strain-wave-gearing\" aria-label=\"strain wave gearing permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>And the last but not least in this list is <strong>strain wave gearing</strong> that is used in the wheels of Apollo Lunar Rover. It requires a flexible spline, but oversteps advantages of the above systems.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/9274e0c7530fdeacb1aebc90fe9fe641/strain_wave_gearing.gif\" alt=\"Strain wave gearing\" title=\"Credit: YouTube channel Akiyuki Brick Channel\"></p>\n<p>\"Credit: YouTube channel Akiyuki Brick Channel\"</p>\n<h2 id=\"micro-gearmotors\" style=\"position:relative;\">Micro gearmotors<a href=\"#micro-gearmotors\" aria-label=\"micro gearmotors permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>For <a href=\"/make/robot/prototype-1\">the first prototype</a> I will try brushed DC micro gear motors with <a href=\"https://www.digikey.com/en/products/detail/pimoroni-ltd/COM0806/6873670\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">75 RPM</a> and <a href=\"https://www.digikey.com/en/products/detail/dfrobot/FIT0483/7087160\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">155 RPM</a>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; flex:1;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4d7b07ef5386d0e43c4f5ee1bc9a9ac6/b4294/micro_gearmotor.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Microgear motor\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4d7b07ef5386d0e43c4f5ee1bc9a9ac6/b4294/micro_gearmotor.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4d7b07ef5386d0e43c4f5ee1bc9a9ac6/d2f63/micro_gearmotor.jpg 163w,\n/static/4d7b07ef5386d0e43c4f5ee1bc9a9ac6/c989d/micro_gearmotor.jpg 325w,\n/static/4d7b07ef5386d0e43c4f5ee1bc9a9ac6/b4294/micro_gearmotor.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><em>Note:</em> voltage defines RPM, not current.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.renesas.com/us/en/support/engineer-school/brushless-dc-motor-01-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Brushless DC motors VS brushed DC motors</a>. Controlling BLDC is not a trivial task, but Field oriented control (FOC) algorithm is not that hard. Look at this <a href=\"https://docs.simplefoc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Arduino implementation</a></p>","excerpt":"Planetary gear train Main question here is power and torque which is created by series of spur gears called a gear train. It could be simple…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#planetary-gear-train\">Planetary gear train</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#epicyclic-gearing\">Epicyclic gearing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#strain-wave-gearing\">Strain wave gearing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#micro-gearmotors\">Micro gearmotors</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"September 24, 2022","published":"December 27, 2022","lastModified":"January 02, 2023","title":"Motors","subtitle":null,"section":"robot","draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/make/robot/motors.md","url":"/make/robot/motors","next":{"excerpt":"Alternatives PCB design alternative LiPo charger from Adafruit Power distribution boards Matek PDB-XT60 w/ BEC 5V & 12V Matek Systems PDB…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/make/robot/power-board.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Power board","date":"2022-10-20T00:00:00.000Z","topi